1
00:00:00,350 --> 00:00:03,160
Look at all these leaves!

2
00:00:03,310 --> 00:00:04,800
Whoa!

3
00:00:05,130 --> 00:00:07,000
Wait, what's going on?

4
00:00:08,640 --> 00:00:11,020
Oh no! It won't go back in!

5
00:00:11,180 --> 00:00:13,000
It's heading over
there! It can't get under!

6
00:00:15,030 --> 00:00:16,230
So noisy.

7
00:00:16,570 --> 00:00:19,159
They always come out more when it rains.

8
00:00:19,160 --> 00:00:20,160
Holy cow!

9
00:00:20,310 --> 00:00:22,690
It's a mole! Look,
it's eating a worm! Whoa!

10
00:00:24,170 --> 00:00:26,180
Can't you guys clean the
yard a bit more quietly?

11
00:00:27,090 --> 00:00:30,420
Oh, Shizuka-san, I'm so sorry.

12
00:00:30,610 --> 00:00:32,250
- No, it's...
- Honestly.

13
00:00:32,410 --> 00:00:34,330
We were having so
much fun, I just lost track...

14
00:00:34,620 --> 00:00:36,060
What are you doing here, Sawada-san?

15
00:00:36,530 --> 00:00:40,400
I was just passing by after shopping.

16
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:41,600
And then?

17
00:00:43,300 --> 00:00:46,920
"I saw poor Saku-chan being bossed around by
you, and I just couldn't stand by and watch."

18
00:00:46,921 --> 00:00:49,830
So you came to help
him out, right, Chizu-chan?

19
00:00:49,930 --> 00:00:53,030
- Chizu-chan...?
- That's right, Saku-chan.

20
00:00:53,130 --> 00:00:54,339
- Saku-chan...
- If we have to do it anyway,

21
00:00:54,340 --> 00:00:55,686
we might as well have a good time.

22
00:00:55,710 --> 00:00:56,710
Right?

23
00:00:58,130 --> 00:00:59,490
You two are something else...

24
00:00:59,980 --> 00:01:03,380
Shizuka-san, you look tired too.

25
00:01:03,840 --> 00:01:04,989
Why don't we all have some tea?

26
00:01:04,990 --> 00:01:05,730
I'm in!

27
00:01:05,740 --> 00:01:07,180
No, I'm fine...

28
00:01:07,610 --> 00:01:10,210
- Come on, don't be shy.
- What do you mean, "don't be shy"?

29
00:01:10,560 --> 00:01:12,060
- This is my house.
- There, there.

30
00:01:13,080 --> 00:01:14,350
Then I'll help myself.

31
00:01:15,090 --> 00:01:17,179
These are delicious. They're my favorite.

32
00:01:17,180 --> 00:01:19,990
- Wow, Chizu-chan, these are great!
- Right?

33
00:01:20,360 --> 00:01:21,619
Where did you get them?

34
00:01:21,620 --> 00:01:22,779
At a place over in Komaba.

35
00:01:22,780 --> 00:01:26,050
- There's a bakery right next to the fruit stand.
- Uh-huh.

36
00:01:26,150 --> 00:01:28,980
- They make them there. Good, aren't they?
- So good.

37
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:30,660
I like this heart-shaped one.

38
00:01:30,820 --> 00:01:32,150
The red is cute, isn't it?

39
00:01:32,160 --> 00:01:33,759
- It is.
- I like this one.

40
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:35,210
So you don't like the heart, then.

41
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:51,500
(Minoru Kuji: Arriving tomorrow at 2 PM)

42
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:08,320
So he's finally coming...

43
00:02:11,110 --> 00:02:12,210
Hey.

44
00:02:12,660 --> 00:02:13,860
I should probably get going...

45
00:02:21,580 --> 00:02:22,580
Hey.

46
00:02:22,660 --> 00:02:23,660
Kuji.

47
00:02:31,610 --> 00:02:32,610
Yeah?

48
00:02:33,310 --> 00:02:34,790
No, I mean...

49
00:02:35,140 --> 00:02:37,370
It's a bit early, but I'm heading out.

50
00:02:41,340 --> 00:02:42,340
Oh.

51
00:02:44,720 --> 00:02:45,720
See ya.

52
00:02:49,240 --> 00:02:52,220
I have to make dinner
for my sister tonight.

53
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:54,120
In that case,

54
00:02:54,440 --> 00:02:56,200
want to take some
leftovers from the fridge?

55
00:02:56,930 --> 00:02:57,970
That would be a huge help.

56
00:02:59,520 --> 00:03:01,290
Well, I'd love to say yes,

57
00:03:01,630 --> 00:03:03,740
but she gave me a very specific list

58
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,680
of what to buy and what to cook.

59
00:03:06,510 --> 00:03:07,760
She's quite the capable sister.

60
00:03:08,310 --> 00:03:10,710
Honestly, she just doesn't trust me.

61
00:03:11,280 --> 00:03:12,280
Well...

62
00:03:13,030 --> 00:03:14,030
That's probably true.

63
00:03:15,360 --> 00:03:17,330
Ouch. You didn't have to agree so fast.

64
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:25,600
You two really get along well.

65
00:03:32,130 --> 00:03:33,130
Hey.

66
00:03:33,850 --> 00:03:36,430
What's your brother like?

67
00:03:39,850 --> 00:03:41,060
He's two years older than me.

68
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:42,510
Straight-A student,

69
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:43,560
star athlete.

70
00:03:45,480 --> 00:03:47,000
Works for a major corporation.

71
00:03:47,790 --> 00:03:49,550
Lives in Boston now with his wife and kid.

72
00:03:51,700 --> 00:03:53,270
He's basically the perfect human being.

73
00:03:55,150 --> 00:03:56,280
Wow.

74
00:03:58,200 --> 00:03:59,300
He sounds impressive.

75
00:04:02,390 --> 00:04:03,560
You should get going.

76
00:04:03,820 --> 00:04:04,820
It's getting late.

77
00:04:06,100 --> 00:04:07,100
Right.

78
00:04:07,620 --> 00:04:08,620
See you later...

79
00:04:16,420 --> 00:04:17,520
Are you okay?

80
00:04:21,150 --> 00:04:22,150
Huh?

81
00:04:23,650 --> 00:04:25,090
As long as you're doing alright.

82
00:04:28,270 --> 00:04:30,130
This guy never changes.

83
00:04:30,700 --> 00:04:31,800
Just like back then.

84
00:04:35,190 --> 00:04:36,290
Are you okay?

85
00:04:41,320 --> 00:04:42,320
What?

86
00:04:47,610 --> 00:04:48,610
And what about me?

87
00:04:49,620 --> 00:04:50,620
How am I doing?

88
00:04:53,620 --> 00:04:54,620
Ah.

89
00:05:08,490 --> 00:05:10,580
You look much better now.

90
00:05:55,700 --> 00:06:01,000
"Life In Smokey Blue"

91
00:06:01,100 --> 00:06:03,400
(Episode 4: Self-Awareness)
(Career Path Survey)

92
00:06:03,410 --> 00:06:05,720
A career path survey, huh?

93
00:06:07,330 --> 00:06:08,740
Is it that time already?

94
00:06:10,190 --> 00:06:11,740
We're only juniors.

95
00:06:12,870 --> 00:06:15,060
I honestly have no idea what I want to do.

96
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:17,560
It's normal to be worried.

97
00:06:18,380 --> 00:06:20,520
I was stressed out of my mind back then.

98
00:06:21,420 --> 00:06:22,420
Hey.

99
00:06:23,290 --> 00:06:25,390
How did you decide what
to do after graduation?

100
00:06:26,760 --> 00:06:27,760
Well...

101
00:06:34,950 --> 00:06:35,950
No good.

102
00:06:36,220 --> 00:06:38,080
I have absolutely no recollection.

103
00:06:39,940 --> 00:06:41,760
That's not helpful at all.

104
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:43,770
I'll tell you if I remember.

105
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:47,220
I'll ask Kuji for you next time, too.

106
00:06:48,920 --> 00:06:49,920
That might be good.

107
00:06:50,570 --> 00:06:51,570
Thanks.

108
00:06:55,590 --> 00:06:56,590
Crap.

109
00:06:56,990 --> 00:06:58,076
I'm gonna be late for my club.

110
00:06:58,100 --> 00:06:59,580
- Good luck.
- I'm off!

111
00:06:59,590 --> 00:07:00,590
See ya.

112
00:07:13,750 --> 00:07:14,860
Higher education, huh...

113
00:07:20,650 --> 00:07:22,090
I should probably...

114
00:07:31,140 --> 00:07:34,830
Thinking about where
my life is going at 38...

115
00:07:52,260 --> 00:07:53,800
I wonder what Kuji thinks.

116
00:07:55,480 --> 00:07:57,550
When he looks at what lies ahead,

117
00:07:59,170 --> 00:08:01,590
does he feel anxious too?

118
00:08:08,430 --> 00:08:09,530
Welcome.

119
00:08:10,510 --> 00:08:11,610
It's been a long time.

120
00:08:11,740 --> 00:08:12,840
Long time no see.

121
00:08:12,990 --> 00:08:14,430
Good to see you, Minoru, Hazuki-san.

122
00:08:17,090 --> 00:08:19,020
Eno-chan, do you remember me?

123
00:08:21,730 --> 00:08:24,969
Sorry for the sudden visit
after being out of touch for so long.

124
00:08:24,970 --> 00:08:27,106
Every time we're back in
the country, it's a whirlwind.

125
00:08:27,130 --> 00:08:28,820
- Here, for you.
- Thank you.

126
00:08:29,350 --> 00:08:30,350
Please, come in.

127
00:08:31,390 --> 00:08:32,670
Eno-chan, you can wear these.

128
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:36,810
Thank you.

129
00:08:39,590 --> 00:08:42,010
- Is this Grandpa's house?
- Yeah.

130
00:08:42,680 --> 00:08:44,660
Are we staying here tonight?

131
00:08:44,890 --> 00:08:45,890
Of course not.

132
00:08:46,150 --> 00:08:48,160
Daddy booked a really nice hotel for us.

133
00:08:48,630 --> 00:08:49,799
It even has a pool.

134
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:50,670
A pool!

135
00:08:50,690 --> 00:08:52,050
Let's go swimming later.

136
00:08:53,380 --> 00:08:54,580
That's amazing, Eno-chan.

137
00:08:54,630 --> 00:08:55,920
You can swim already?

138
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:57,630
I'm not that good yet...

139
00:08:58,200 --> 00:08:59,526
What are you talking
about? That's not true.

140
00:08:59,550 --> 00:09:01,750
You worked so hard to
learn the freestyle, didn't you?

141
00:09:02,680 --> 00:09:07,680
Daddy thinks you're the
best swimmer in the world.

142
00:09:08,270 --> 00:09:10,439
You worked hard because

143
00:09:10,440 --> 00:09:12,300
- Daddy was cheering for you, right?
- Yeah!

144
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:15,320
Compared to my brilliant brother,

145
00:09:16,260 --> 00:09:17,910
I've always felt inferior.

146
00:09:18,380 --> 00:09:20,459
Eno, the grown-ups
have things to talk about.

147
00:09:20,460 --> 00:09:21,750
Want to go on an adventure?

148
00:09:21,820 --> 00:09:22,820
Okay!

149
00:09:22,890 --> 00:09:24,730
That sounds like a plan. Go ahead.

150
00:09:28,150 --> 00:09:29,670
The garden is just around that corner.

151
00:09:44,870 --> 00:09:47,010
I haven't been back here

152
00:09:49,480 --> 00:09:50,840
since Dad's funeral two years ago.

153
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:53,200
Yeah.

154
00:09:54,950 --> 00:09:56,600
Still the same dark,

155
00:09:57,250 --> 00:09:58,890
gloomy house.

156
00:10:13,460 --> 00:10:14,460
Ugh.

157
00:10:15,980 --> 00:10:18,760
It smells like cigarettes
and moldy old books.

158
00:10:22,520 --> 00:10:25,000
What are you going to do with all these?

159
00:10:25,360 --> 00:10:27,120
It'll cost a fortune
just to clear them out.

160
00:10:28,380 --> 00:10:31,070
I doubt any university
would take them these days.

161
00:10:39,640 --> 00:10:41,210
Leaving stuff like this behind

162
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:42,860
is just a burden on everyone else.

163
00:10:45,310 --> 00:10:46,150
Minoru.

164
00:10:46,310 --> 00:10:48,560
I can't even breathe in here.

165
00:10:55,030 --> 00:10:57,120
Damn it, what's wrong with this thing?

166
00:11:06,770 --> 00:11:07,770
Let me try.

167
00:11:11,030 --> 00:11:12,150
You have to do it like this.

168
00:11:12,710 --> 00:11:14,510
Lift it up a bit before you slide it.

169
00:11:26,980 --> 00:11:28,610
I've never seen this view before...

170
00:11:32,930 --> 00:11:33,930
Daddy!

171
00:11:35,010 --> 00:11:36,010
Hey.

172
00:11:36,590 --> 00:11:37,590
Eno.

173
00:11:37,750 --> 00:11:40,040
What kind of house do
you want to live in here?

174
00:11:40,940 --> 00:11:44,070
Hmm... a white house!

175
00:11:44,670 --> 00:11:45,840
Alright.

176
00:11:46,250 --> 00:11:47,250
Then right here,

177
00:11:47,540 --> 00:11:50,030
let's build a big, white house.

178
00:12:15,900 --> 00:12:18,500
A burden, huh...

179
00:12:35,580 --> 00:12:36,790
When I was a child,

180
00:12:37,730 --> 00:12:40,550
in this room where I
wasn't even allowed to enter,

181
00:12:43,470 --> 00:12:45,230
we sat together and
wove words into stories.

182
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:49,120
That's where I learned
what it meant to "work."

183
00:12:51,070 --> 00:12:53,390
Living with my father...

184
00:13:00,770 --> 00:13:01,970
This was the only place

185
00:13:02,790 --> 00:13:04,780
where he would finally look me in the eye.

186
00:13:09,470 --> 00:13:11,210
How did the talk with the lawyer go?

187
00:13:12,310 --> 00:13:13,680
No major issues.

188
00:13:13,870 --> 00:13:15,180
Shizuka agreed to everything.

189
00:13:15,670 --> 00:13:18,510
We can handle the rest online
once I'm back in Boston.

190
00:13:19,077 --> 00:13:20,077
That's good.

191
00:13:21,190 --> 00:13:23,500
Sorry for dragging you
along for all this today.

192
00:13:23,700 --> 00:13:24,930
You must be exhausted, Hazuki.

193
00:13:25,180 --> 00:13:26,180
Not at all.

194
00:13:26,190 --> 00:13:30,170
I wanted to pay my respects to
your parents. I'm glad we could come.

195
00:13:30,860 --> 00:13:31,860
I see.

196
00:13:34,090 --> 00:13:35,490
I guess so.

197
00:13:40,650 --> 00:13:41,650
Are you okay?

198
00:13:41,980 --> 00:13:42,980
Hmm?

199
00:13:43,670 --> 00:13:44,670
What do you mean?

200
00:13:45,770 --> 00:13:47,920
I don't know... you just seem a little off.

201
00:13:57,670 --> 00:13:58,770
Being back here...

202
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:02,110
it's always painful.

203
00:14:03,540 --> 00:14:04,640
Why is it painful?

204
00:14:06,550 --> 00:14:08,310
Because ever since we were kids,

205
00:14:08,980 --> 00:14:11,240
Dad only ever had eyes for Shizuka.

206
00:14:14,830 --> 00:14:16,350
Back in elementary school,

207
00:14:17,390 --> 00:14:18,750
Shizuka was always at the library,

208
00:14:19,260 --> 00:14:21,540
bringing home mountains of books.

209
00:14:23,020 --> 00:14:24,770
Dad would see that and just beam with joy.

210
00:14:26,820 --> 00:14:29,380
He'd say things like,
"You're really something else, aren't you?"

211
00:14:34,210 --> 00:14:36,710
But even when I was top of my class,

212
00:14:37,910 --> 00:14:39,910
or when I won swimming competitions,

213
00:14:41,700 --> 00:14:43,660
he never even looked at me.

214
00:14:50,060 --> 00:14:51,060
Today,

215
00:14:52,010 --> 00:14:53,630
I was reminded of that all over again.

216
00:14:56,120 --> 00:14:58,020
That room with the beautiful view...

217
00:14:59,420 --> 00:15:01,550
In the end, he never once let me inside.

218
00:15:05,970 --> 00:15:07,070
Minoru...

219
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:17,860
And I know it's not Shizuka's fault...

220
00:15:34,630 --> 00:15:36,000
Memories etched

221
00:15:37,450 --> 00:15:38,450
into the pillars,

222
00:15:39,850 --> 00:15:40,850
into the walls,

223
00:15:41,740 --> 00:15:42,740
into the floors.

224
00:15:45,328 --> 00:15:46,689
In every single corner of this house.

225
00:15:46,690 --> 00:15:49,270
- Thanks for having us.
- See you later!

226
00:15:49,330 --> 00:15:50,330
Goodbye.

227
00:15:53,100 --> 00:15:55,250
Next time we see each
other, we'll be moving back.

228
00:15:55,940 --> 00:15:58,000
Make sure you find a new place by then.

229
00:15:59,280 --> 00:16:00,280
Yeah.

230
00:16:01,800 --> 00:16:02,800
Alright, see ya.

231
00:16:06,560 --> 00:16:07,760
- Shizuka...
- Minoru...

232
00:16:12,550 --> 00:16:13,550
No...

233
00:16:15,530 --> 00:16:17,020
Never mind. It's nothing.

234
00:16:17,560 --> 00:16:18,560
What about you?

235
00:16:23,680 --> 00:16:24,780
Safe travels...

236
00:16:26,460 --> 00:16:27,460
Ah.

237
00:16:28,010 --> 00:16:29,010
Thanks.

238
00:16:33,890 --> 00:16:35,130
Scars of our own.

239
00:16:52,440 --> 00:16:53,540
Coming in!

240
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:00,560
What is it?

241
00:17:00,950 --> 00:17:02,190
What do you mean, "what is it"?

242
00:17:02,580 --> 00:17:04,070
I'm finished with today's work.

243
00:17:05,360 --> 00:17:06,630
Here, take a look.

244
00:17:09,520 --> 00:17:11,240
Did you actually check it yourself first?

245
00:17:11,640 --> 00:17:13,090
Of course I did, Shizuka.

246
00:17:15,370 --> 00:17:16,370
I'll look at it.

247
00:17:17,260 --> 00:17:18,260
Oh.

248
00:17:18,650 --> 00:17:19,650
By the way,

249
00:17:24,300 --> 00:17:25,650
that book I reserved...

250
00:17:26,480 --> 00:17:27,720
could you go pick it up for me?

251
00:17:29,170 --> 00:17:30,170
Sure, sure.

252
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:05,200
Oh, this one...

253
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:15,200
Looks interesting.

254
00:18:17,020 --> 00:18:18,530
I'm back.

255
00:18:24,920 --> 00:18:26,120
I'm home.

256
00:18:27,550 --> 00:18:29,100
That bookstore was way out there.

257
00:18:29,550 --> 00:18:31,840
What now? I thought you
said work was over for the day.

258
00:18:32,880 --> 00:18:34,770
- I just finished checking it.
- And?

259
00:18:35,160 --> 00:18:36,850
- Yeah, it's fine.
- See?

260
00:18:37,320 --> 00:18:38,320
Here.

261
00:18:39,630 --> 00:18:40,630
Oh, and this too.

262
00:18:42,330 --> 00:18:43,330
Thanks for the hard work.

263
00:18:54,620 --> 00:18:55,720
Closing the family grave?

264
00:18:56,440 --> 00:18:58,160
It seems to be happening more often lately.

265
00:18:59,109 --> 00:19:00,789
When there's no one
left to look after them,

266
00:19:01,470 --> 00:19:04,230
families decide to relocate the remains.

267
00:19:06,210 --> 00:19:07,660
Times are changing, I guess.

268
00:19:08,980 --> 00:19:09,760
Wait a second.

269
00:19:09,761 --> 00:19:12,210
Do you really need to
report every single thing?

270
00:19:13,840 --> 00:19:14,940
Is it a relative?

271
00:19:15,270 --> 00:19:16,270
No.

272
00:19:17,750 --> 00:19:18,750
But, well...

273
00:19:19,470 --> 00:19:21,070
I've been visiting the grave every year.

274
00:19:22,030 --> 00:19:23,030
Huh?

275
00:19:28,050 --> 00:19:29,620
Yoshie Kimitsu...

276
00:19:31,850 --> 00:19:34,300
Was that the doctor you
worked with as a rep?

277
00:19:37,880 --> 00:19:39,100
It was Dr. Kimitsu.

278
00:19:40,930 --> 00:19:42,130
I see...

279
00:19:45,210 --> 00:19:47,300
He must have been a very kind doctor,

280
00:19:48,340 --> 00:19:50,550
always putting his patients first.

281
00:19:52,700 --> 00:19:53,700
Yeah.

282
00:19:55,010 --> 00:19:57,430
His motto was always
"Everything for the patient."

283
00:19:59,950 --> 00:20:01,760
He always put himself last.

284
00:20:03,710 --> 00:20:05,580
Even when he was so busy he barely slept,

285
00:20:06,480 --> 00:20:07,750
he would still take the time

286
00:20:08,330 --> 00:20:09,770
to really listen to someone like me.

287
00:20:13,060 --> 00:20:14,460
That's truly rare.

288
00:20:15,250 --> 00:20:16,350
A doctor like that...

289
00:20:19,230 --> 00:20:21,230
Because I respected him so much,

290
00:20:23,850 --> 00:20:25,540
it really hit me hard back then.

291
00:20:34,430 --> 00:20:35,530
Are you okay?

292
00:20:40,630 --> 00:20:41,630
What?

293
00:20:56,520 --> 00:20:57,520
But back then,

294
00:20:59,380 --> 00:21:01,550
I couldn't even let myself feel sad.

295
00:21:09,170 --> 00:21:10,170
At the time,

296
00:21:11,340 --> 00:21:13,360
I couldn't face my own weakness.

297
00:21:16,690 --> 00:21:17,890
In these past eight years,

298
00:21:18,820 --> 00:21:20,680
have I grown at all?

299
00:21:24,270 --> 00:21:25,560
Who knows.

300
00:21:27,740 --> 00:21:28,740
At the very least,

301
00:21:30,180 --> 00:21:32,070
I'm able to let myself feel sad now.

302
00:21:34,590 --> 00:21:35,590
I see.

303
00:21:39,660 --> 00:21:41,150
This guy hasn't changed a bit.

304
00:21:42,340 --> 00:21:43,340
Ever since then,

305
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:46,920
even when he knows exactly what's going on,

306
00:21:47,660 --> 00:21:49,850
he just pretends he doesn't
and quietly stays by my side.

307
00:21:55,280 --> 00:21:56,280
Thank you.

308
00:21:58,110 --> 00:21:59,210
For back then,

309
00:22:00,010 --> 00:22:01,110
and for now.

310
00:22:05,900 --> 00:22:08,070
You're being way too
honest. It's creeping me out.

311
00:22:09,700 --> 00:22:10,800
I knew you'd say that.

312
00:22:11,170 --> 00:22:14,180
I can't believe you remember
all that stuff from so long ago.

313
00:22:17,790 --> 00:22:21,050
Wait... do you actually
like me or something?

314
00:22:23,340 --> 00:22:25,780
Yeah, I guess I do.

315
00:22:31,090 --> 00:22:32,190
Oh, so that's how it is.

316
00:22:37,330 --> 00:22:38,330
That's funny.

317
00:22:48,940 --> 00:22:50,040
Etched away, bit by bit,

318
00:22:52,380 --> 00:22:53,960
everyone's emotions

319
00:22:54,650 --> 00:22:55,750
remain here in this house.

320
00:23:00,450 --> 00:23:02,076
(Next Episode)
If you go back right now,

321
00:23:02,100 --> 00:23:03,610
Kuji's going to be lonely.

322
00:23:03,890 --> 00:23:05,030
Then I'll stay for a bit.

323
00:23:05,800 --> 00:23:07,010
You're exaggerating.

324
00:23:07,130 --> 00:23:08,230
Winter...?

325
00:23:08,460 --> 00:23:09,460
That's unusual.

326
00:23:09,780 --> 00:23:11,630
Once this glossary is finished,

327
00:23:12,660 --> 00:23:13,860
I'm thinking of quitting.
